This paper discusses techniques for combining multiple feature sets and decisions obtained from medical images, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the practical applications of these techniques in medical imaging, which could fall under human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques for feature and data fusion. Finally, the paper discusses the importance of robustness and accuracy in these techniques, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
